title: OKC CX Presented by Team PG13
Battle at the Bird MTB Race - TdD #1
Tulsa Wheelmen Summer Crit Training Series
Central Oklahoma Summer Race Series June 2009
Team PG13 Time Trial
course: An open, relatively flat, point to point course starting 1.5 miles north from the Lake Draper Marina on the West side of the lake. The distance is approximately 11 miles.
registration:
Race Day Registration Only Starts at 8:30am and Ends at 9:30am 
Registration will be located at the Lake Draper Marina Parking Lot
Race starts approximately 1.5 miles north of Marina.
notes: All proceeds will be donated to the Young Survival Coalition to help fight Breast Cancer in young women. There will be 100.00 cash for the fastest individual time and swag for the categories. All results will be reported to USA Cycling for scoring.
directions: Contact Eldon Harding for Directions. pg13graphics@me.com or 405-720-8002

title: Roman Nose Mountain Bike Festival - TdD #5
Blue Canyon Oklahoma Championship Time Trial
Central Oklahoma Summer Race Series August 2009
Red Dirt Rendezvous - TdD #7
description: The Red Dirt Rendezvous takes place once again at Oklahoma City\\\'s Lake Stanley Draper MOuntain Bike Park. The typical spring event has been moved to the fall this year. Look for over 25 categories competing for excellent prizes, a guaranteed expert payout, and points towards the Tour de Dirt championship series. It is about racing, but while you are not on the tight twisty trails, have fun with bike toss, log pull, and time trial in the second annual Har-d-Har-Har games.  FREE kids races as part of the Al\'s Bicycles Kids Kup.
course: Overall, look for tight twisty in-the-woods trail with a bit of double track to faciliate passing. A multi-lap short course on the green for the beginners Cat 3, wth Cat 1 and 2 riding most of the trails on a 10 mile loop including some of the new blue section opened this spring.
registration: Register Saturday at the venue from 11-2PM, Sunday before the races we will open at 7:30 AM, or online.
notes: No water or electricity is at the MTB park.  Water and sports drink will be made avaiable.  No camping on the grounds, but there is at the Draper Marina. PARKING will be on the northbound lane of Post road.
directions: SE OKC south of I-240 on the East side of Post Road
